reviews.text: I love everything about the store especially the frozen foods. They're healthy, easy to prepare and reasonably priced. During the work days, I pick something up with maybe a salad or a loaf of bread for an easy to prepare meal for my family. What's great is that there's a good selection of frozen ethnic foods! We're always trying something new. Meal times are exciting!

This is a great place to buy groceries. Some of the health food grocery stores have a terrible reputation about being overpriced and having a strange and rare selection. Trader Joe's has a beautiful basic medium roast coffee that's $5 a pound. You can buy wine there at a very reasonable price and you can buy by the case. The produce section is amazing and comparable with everyone else's prices. If you like cheese this is the one place in the city to go to. They have some beautiful rare cave aged Swiss cheese and it's really good. they have five kinds of cheese there that you might have trouble pronouncing their names. It's an amazing selection. And on a strange aesthetic side point some of the most handsome men in the city seem to work there all the time. It's easy on the eyes and very friendly.

I love Trader Joe's! I think it's more affordable than Whole Foods. I don't think there is nothing not to like about it. I bought a bunch of wine when I was there mostly for cooking. You can't beat the two buck chuck though it's not that anymore. Still the price is good.

I moved from NYC 5 months ago and my Trader Joe's experience has changed tremendously. When I go the staff is delightful. Whenever I can't find an item either they get it for me or when they run out they let me know what days the product might be coming in. I've been getting consistent wonderful customer service since I started coming to this location. you won't regret coming in.

Even though its extremely hard to find a decent supply chain for vegan organic food, they actually do a decent job at it! I find great deals on organic produce like bagged organic apples and potatoes when I'm there. Sometimes they're a bit bruised but I use them for juicing and for the price that is acceptable. Basically they just buy up unsaleable lots from other health food stores and resell them. Kind of an outlet mall for natural foods. One thing I disapprove of.. is there's an obnoxiously large liquor department taking up half the store. And everything being packaged does add an element of wastefulness, it would be nice to see a bulk bins section. The cashiers are above and beyond friendly and helpful though and the atmosphere and location of the store are both ideal. Overall they are one of the best options in town!

I happen to be a wicked famous person here in Boston.  I like Spikes. I was there when it opened. I eat the junk yard dogs. Chili fries are good too.  The place is like wicked clean too.  They got their own root beer and stuff. Five stars mates

I used to stop here as a young twenty something after the bars. Always loved the staff, atmosphere and most of all the dogs. Menu is more than hot dogs but with so many custom dogs on the menu I don't think I ever tried anything else.  I have since moved away and grown older...... today while in town I could not resist a junkyard dog. Went with my favorite the Texas ranger dog with fries. It did not disappoint.  Even after all these years and hyped expectations it tasted so good,still my favorite dog. Ps the Fries are good to. Thanks Dave!
Great local hotdogs, burgers and chicken shop. Fresh, tasty icon of Boston’s best. Driving by and stopped. Dave’s a personal friendly owner.
Spike s is my favorite place for gourmet hot dogs and chili fries.  I am like a wicked pissa famous person in Boston so I know where to go. Super friendly service and wicked clean too
Great customer service. And amazing cookies. Decent food

Extremely good Thai food at reasonable prices. 

The chrispy duck salad with cashew nuts is a must. The curries and duck are the specialty of the restaurant.
Amazing thai food!

전통있는 유명한 식당이다.
상도 받았던 것으로 기억한다.
음식의 양은 그리 많지 않다.
깔끔하게 음식이 나온다.
아쉽지만 가격은 조금 나간다. ^^
落ち着いて、タイ料理が楽しめます。数十年前から変わらない味が嬉しいですね。
雰囲気は良いですが、味は普通で値段高いです^^;

Quick stop for some "fro-yo". There were many choices of yogurt and also toppings. The price was very reasonable, especially when you give the 11 year old free reign to make his own sundae. Very clean inside, would go back.

Excellent great food great service

Thank you very much we had an amazing experience here and the food was amazing. We had great Service, If you want to be treated like a valued guest this is the spot for you. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a solid meal. You did not feel rushed you could enjoy your meal. The food was delicious, and the prices are reasonable as well. We will be returning soon.

Just getting around to describing the experience. Came in for my two year anniversary. Service was attentive and food was great. However they placed us at a table that was less than half the size of every other table around us that was located less than two feet from the couple next to us. Looking around, EVERYONE had a nice luxurious space by comparison. Like literally every other table I spotted had at least 4 feet around them and was a normal size. Our table was very obviously set up to maximize their tables on Valentine's Day, and we spent our dinner being passed on all sides by servers. It's disheartening to make reservations at an "upscale" location paying 50 bucks a person to not even be able to talk to my girlfriend across the table from me with any shred of privacy. Shame on you Eleven Forty Nine, would not recommend.

I took my bestie to 1149 for a Birthday Brunch.  Our server Melissa was very nice and checked on us often but not too often nor not enough....she was perfect.  However, the brunch costs 31.95 per person.  At that cost everything should be fresh.  Eggs were powdered and even the omelet I ordered, which came nice and hot was powdered eggs.  I don't think the cost matches the food.

Outstanding dinning experience whether for lunch or dinner you can't go wrong.  Friendly and attentive staff, outstanding food and reasonably priced.  I have been there for private functions as well as on y own and have never been disappointed always hits the mark which is tough in the restaurant business.  Well done and worth a visit any time.. great place to take clients for a drink and apps also!!!

Eleven Forty Nine pulls out all the stops with their super delicious lobster risotto, big portion, lots of seafood and generally amazing flavor. The bar menu is excellent and this is a great place to take someone for a somewhat special occasion, either business, romance or just a special weekend.

We had the calamari and seared tuna appetizers, which with both packed full of flavor and came out quickly. We had a somewhat large group, and were impressed by the service, especially the speed that everything came out and the fact that our drinks were never empty.

Beer selection here is good, with a couple of good go to flavors for almost any pallet, though I can’t comment on the wine and I unfortunately didn’t make it to dessert, as I was quite thoroughly stuffed after the main entree!

This would be a great place to take a date if you’re looking to impress, or for any slightly more upscale dinners!
